reviewText: Video features Rudolf Firkusny, Yo-Yo Ma, Itzhak Perlman, Frederica von Stade, the Prague Philharmonic Chorus, the Boston Symphony Orchestra conducted by Seiji Ozawa in magnificent performances of Dvorak's master  works including: Carnival Overture, excerpts from "New World  Symphony", Humoresque in E flat minor, "Dumsky" trio and  Slavonic Dance in E minor. I think it aired on PBS.
